# Example npm registry auth for the ui-webapp build (BuildKit secret id=npmrc).
#
# Copy this file to `npmrc` in this directory and fill in real values:
#     cp config/secrets/npmrc.example config/secrets/npmrc
# `npmrc` is gitignored. It is mounted to /root/.npmrc on a tmpfs only during
# `npm ci` (src/frontend-angular/Dockerfile) — never written to an image layer
# or the build cache. Leave absent for public builds (no auth needed).
#
# Use the SCOPED form below; modern npm ignores the legacy unscoped `_auth=`.
# The scope (host + path) must match NPM_REGISTRY exactly, trailing slash
# included. These are the lines `npm login` writes — copy them verbatim.

//repo.artifactory-gogent.group.echonet/artifactory/api/npm/npm/:_auth=BASE64_OF_USER_PASSWORD
//repo.artifactory-gogent.group.echonet/artifactory/api/npm/npm/:always-auth=true

# If Artifactory issued a token instead of a user:password pair, use _authToken
# in place of the :_auth line above:
# //repo.artifactory-gogent.group.echonet/artifactory/api/npm/npm/:_authToken=YOUR_TOKEN
